<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2016]" box="[199,641,1593,1620]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1593,1620]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Distribution.</emphasis>
S 
<collectingCountry box="[382,449,1593,1619]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[464,536,1593,1620]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Hubei</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation box="[558,627,1593,1620]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1350,1375]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,524,1324]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,524,1324]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Chinese Lamiogethes treated herein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3614547" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3614547/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1630,1656]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Host-plants.</emphasis>
Unknown, but certainly among 
<taxonomicName box="[711,836,1629,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
. The above cited 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1218,1629,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosifolius">
<emphasis box="[1036,1218,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Rubus rosifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1234,1343,1629,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
) was an occasional food-plant before or after the flowering season of the species’ larval host. Some other Chinese species of the somewhat related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirejtshuk" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[394,667,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kasparyani">
<emphasis box="[394,667,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Lamiogethes kasparyani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, appear to be associated as larvae to 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1238,1702,1727]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Lamium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1238,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Lamium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1429,1701,1728]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
) and related genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Audisio, P. &amp; Jelinek, J. &amp; Cooter, J." box="[371,590,1737,1764]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" pagination="111 - 127" refId="ref8659" refString="Audisio, P., Jelinek, J. &amp; Cooter, J. (2005) New and little-known species of Meligethes Stephens, 1830 from China (Coleoptera: Nitidulidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 45, 111 - 127." type="journal article" year="2005">
Audisio 
<emphasis box="[468,525,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
; Liu 
<emphasis box="[648,697,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">et al</emphasis>
. unpublished data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1773,1800]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Habitat.</emphasis>
Locality data suggest this species prefers the edges of high altitude sparsely forested and bushy areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1846,1872]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Phenology.</emphasis>
The few available specimens were collected in middle June, which likely indicates adult activity at least from May to July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1918,1944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[851,912,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">hasta</emphasis>
(= lance), due to its peculiarly lance-shaped or sword-tip-shaped apex of the median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[777,861,1953,1980]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[189,1386,205,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[182,1406,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia (tegmen and median lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view) of Lamiogethes spp.: a–b, L. falcatus sp. n., male from China, Sichuan; c–d, L. hastipenis sp. n., male from China, Hubei; e–f, L. sagittalis sp. n., male from China, Shaanxi; g–h, L. unditibiis sp. n., male from China, Chongqing; i–j, L. limaelytralis sp. n., male from China, Sichuan. Scale bar: 0.2 mm (Figs. a–j)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3614541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3614541/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,261,2016]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,153,395]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1989,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
As reported above, this new species is vaguely similar in external shape to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brisout de Barneville" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1308,1436,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buyssoni">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">L. buyssoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Audisio, P." box="[351,505,153,179]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" refId="ref8387" refString="Audisio, P. (1993) Coleoptera Nitidulidae - Kateretidae. Fauna d'Italia. 32. Edizioni, Calderini, Bologna, 971 pp." type="book" year="1993">Audisio 1993</bibRefCitation>
), as well as to other E Palearctic species of the genus, but is more closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio, 2020" authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,269,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,269,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[276,335,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
described above, sharing with the latter an overall similar body shape and size, 
<typeStatus box="[1226,1274,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">type</typeStatus>
of punctation, and peculiarly sword-tip-shaped distal apex of the median lobe of aedeagus. Male specimens of the latter species are different in possessing metatibiae arcuately curved (simple in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio" authorityYear="2020" box="[840,982,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastipenis">
<emphasis box="[840,982,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. hastipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), much wider protarsi and protibiae, less strongly impressed metaventrite, and markedly different tegmen. As discussed above, 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio, 2020" authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio" authorityYear="2020" box="[1117,1235,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1117,1235,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1242,1303,297,323]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio, 2020" authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastipenis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. hastipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[191,252,333,359]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio, 2020" authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio" authorityYear="2020" box="[265,398,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittalis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[265,398,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. sagittalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[404,464,333,359]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio, 2020" authorityName="Liu &amp; Yang &amp; Huang &amp; Cline &amp; Sabatelli &amp; Audisio" authorityYear="2020" box="[519,655,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unditibiis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[519,655,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. unditibiis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[662,722,333,359]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belong to the same species complex, also including 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kirejtshuk" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[1310,1436,334,359]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Lamiogethes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancestor">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">L. ancestor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from central E 
<collectingCountry box="[320,391,369,395]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
